Requires ~build.requires to make parser module available at runtime

The parser COMPILES correctly into backend.zig, but when output_emitted.zig
tries to @import("parser"), it fails because the output build doesn't include
the parser module.

SOLUTION: Implement ~build.requires("parser") to inject module dependencies
into the generated build.zig for the final output.

This test documents that:
1. Parser.init signature is now fixed (5 args)
2. Parser wrapper imports work at compile time
3. Runtime usage needs ~build.requires feature
